reviews.review_text: This is unfortunate Ive always been waited on by a wonderful older couple Very knowledgeable about the products and very helpful. The last time I was there it was a fairly young girl. She acually LIED to me about products and when I pointed out that No What she was trying to sell me as a fine pate (the only thing my fussy boy will eat ) But a chunky type that he wouldnt eat She LAUGHED Im sincerely hoping this was a summer hire and will soon be back at school With so many products in thier store its important to buy the right ones Thats why I pay high prices Knowledgeable information ftom staff !!!

As a previous customer for both cat and dog food at this Bosley location, I telephoned the owner who had previously helped me choose the cat food and who previously been welcoming. I advised him that I had discovered an infestation of what looked like beetles and some small caterpillars inside the cat food I had recently purchased. These insects were both over one centimetre long. When I went to return the food I expected the same welcoming manner and an apology. Instead I was asked for the original packaging and receiptas the owner of the shop looked very slowly at the package of the food and treated me like I had just walked of the street looking for a favour. The owner behaved as if he didnt recognize me and even started to challeng me suggesting that the beetles might have even come from inside my house. This is curtomer service? Customer service is also when the owner of the shop accept responsibility for the product he sells and honours his customers loyalty. I am upset and disappointed with Bosleys.
Racist.
